Traffic control measures will be put in place at the Kizhuthalli junction on the National Highway here in view of recurrent road accidents and casualties occurring in the area.The decision was taken at a meeting convened by District Collector P. Bala Kiran on Thursday. Local residents and family members of a person who died in an accident in the area had staged a protest on the road with the body of the deceased on Wednesday.It was decided at the meeting that the undergrowth on either side of the road would be cleared and a concrete footpath would be paved.